  "texts": [
    "When semantic fibrosis information is available to the network, the nodule malignancy classification accuracy increases 5.23%.",
    "Nodule volume doubling time (VDT) as the current clinical guideline to predict nodule malignancy is also included in the experiment for comparison.",
    "The VDT method achieved 62.63%, 56.52%, and 65.48% of accuracy, sensitivity, and specificity respectively.",
    "Note that CNN trained with nodule-only images still outperformed the VDT method.The 3D AG-Net was also trained with the in-house dataset to predict lung fibrosis using the ground-truth fibrosis diagnosis provided by radiologists (fibrosis as 1, non-fibrosis as 0).",
    "The model achieved 73.01 ± 5.84%, 75.18 ± 13.32%, 70.83 ± 6.22%, and 0.75 ± 0.07 for accuracy, sensitivity, specificity, and AUC, respectively."
  ],
